<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/331> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #331" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "It is uncertain whether the fragment (ILS 9338, 3) refers to Pontiffs or Augurs since no. 3 refers to Augurs (see 40 B.C.) and no. 4 to Pontiffs (see 89 and 88). If the above identification is correct the omission of his grandfather's praenomen and his own cognomina are surprising (Dessau, loc. cit.). For the name, see Fast. Cap. on 418." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/330> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #330" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Servilius succeeded Sp. Postumius.\n     ILS 9338, 2- CIL 6.37161.\n     On Postumius, see Lübker no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/329> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #329" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "It is uncertain whether the fragment (ILS 9338, 3) refers to Pontiffs or Augurs since no. 3 refers to Augurs (see 40 B.C.) and no. 4 to Pontiffs (see 89 and 88). If the above identification is correct the omission of his grandfather's praenomen and his own cognomina are surprising (Dessau, loc. cit.). For the name, see Fast. Cap. on 418." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/328> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #328" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Servilius succeeded Sp. Postumius.\n     ILS 9338, 2- CIL 6.37161.\n     On Postumius, see Lübker no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/291> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #291" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under the Consuls against the Volscians (Liv. 3.70.2-5). On Postumius, see Lübker no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/260> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #260" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prepared and caused the enactment of ten tables of laws (Cic. Rep. 2.61; Liv. 3.33.1-36.2; Diod. 12.23.1; Dion. Hal. 10.56.1-2; Tac. Ann. 3.27; Gell. 11.18.6; 17.21.15; 20.1; Dig. 1.2.2.3-4 and 24; Zon. 7.18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/259> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #259" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "{Gr} Mss. AB, Dion. Hal. 10.56.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/252> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #252" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. preserves all or part of eight names, omitting Sestius and Curiatius, Fast. Cap. all or part of six with space for the rest, those of Sestius, Curiatius, Romilius and Postumius, which are supplied from the information on their consulships (Degrassi 26f., 94, 364f.). According to Dion. Hal. (10.56.2) they were all consulars, but this principle was not applied consistently in Livy or Fast. Cap. See notes 3 and 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/249> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #249" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Their return this year led to the creation of the Decemvirate in 451 (Liv. 3.32.6-7, and 33.5; Dion. Hal. 10.54.2-56.1; Zon. 7.18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/241> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #241" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Athens and other Greek cities to study their laws (Liv. 3.31.7-8; Dion. Hal. 10.52.3, cf. 51.1-6; Lyd.) Magg. 1.34; Zon. 7.18; cf. Jerome Chr. on 452 B.C., p. 112 Helm)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/197> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #197" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ILS 9338, 2 ([-Postu]mius A. f. P. n. Albus [- - -]); coopted this year. See 439, note 4; Degrassi 91; Lübker nos. 17 and 16, respectively." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/196> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #196" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "ILS 9338, 2 ([-Postu]mius A. f. P. n. Albus [- - -]); coopted this year. See 439, note 4; Degrassi 91; Lübker nos. 17 and 16, respectively." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/174> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #174" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 3.2.1; Diod. 11.75.1; Fast. Cap. (Sp. Postumius A. f. P. n. Albus Regi [- - -]); Dion. Hal. 9.60.1; Chr. 354 (Rigilliense et Prisco II); Fast. Hyd. (Regilliano et Fusco), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 24f., 91, 358f. Servilius held command against the Aequi (Liv. 3.2.1; Dion. Hal. 9.60.7), while Postumius dedicated the temple of the Dius Fidius (Dion. Hal. 9.60.8; cf. Ovid Fasti 6.213-8; CIL 1\n     , p. 319). On Postumius, see Lübker, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/173> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #173" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Servilius, see 468. The cognomen Structus may not have appeared in Fast. Cap. for 468 or 466 (Degrassi 91). The name of Postumius is preserved almost in full in Fast. Cap. I have listed them in the order given by Liv. and Diod.; the reverse order appears in Dion. Hal. and Fast. Cap." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/108> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #108" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to dedicate the temple of Castor (Liv. 2.42.5; cf. Iordan, Topogr. 1.2.370). See Lübker, no. 16 or 17." .
